article_title: Crews Respond After Grass Fire Flares Up Near Small Lincoln Coun - News9.com - Oklahoma City, OK - News, Weather, Video and Sports
article_text:
Firefighters are working to get a handle on a large grass fire burning near the small community of Jacktown, Okla. in Lincoln County, on Monday.

Jacktown is located near the intersection of State Highways 62 and 177, in between Harrah and Meeker.

The fire appears to have been caused by workers using Bobcats in a a very rural area dense with cedar trees. No structures are being threatened.
